# Stray Go build artifacts at repo root.
# Every `cmd/<name>/` can produce a binary called `<name>`. `make build` uses
# `-o ./build/<name>` correctly; a bare `go build ./cmd/<name>` does NOT and
# drops the binary at repo root, where it is not otherwise ignored. These
# explicit entries are the safety net for that mistake — keep this list in
# sync with `ls cmd/`. The rule (CLAUDE.md): never `go build` without
# `-o ./build/<name>`.
/collector
/doctor
/migrator
/notifier
/wasm
/web

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test
cmd/debug
docs/swagger
dist

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# IDE configs
.idea
.vscode

# Environment variables
.env

# AI workspace files
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/README.md

*.logs
*.log.md
# Embedded static assets (generated by make build)
cmd/web/tmp/app.wasm
cmd/web/tmp/wasm_exec.js
